<br />
Ok, so here&#39;s an attempt at post-rotation telepathy. The base of which is pretty similar to most telepathy decks that you&#39;ve probably seen before. Basically the strat is to use Gandy MoW, Forearmed, Glimpse of Fate to shrink down minions. The elves then hopefully overwhelm the minions and move pretty easily. <br />
Galadriel only will have 9 resistance, so <!--284-->Glamdring and Watch and Wait will hopefully keep the burdens off. Corruption/resistance may be this deck&#39;s toughest matchup. <br />
Elrond and Gandalf set up huge Attonement combos with their abilities. <br />
That is No Orc Horn and Shadow Between try and keep my Elves free of wounds, but I think a little more might be needed in this department. I badly want to put in Must Be a Dream as my main healing, but I&#39;m not sure it is trustworthy enough. <br />
So the goal here is to get some input on this deck. Basically I&#39;m looking to trim as much as possible. It will probably go with a nazgul deck so the forearmed will pay off.<br />
